    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.49.1" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">1</fw>
                <note type="curatorial">Aly Collection</note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                Skyrim Farm 
                Route #7                  
                <hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA, MO.</hi>
                
                May 25, 1966
                    </dateline>
                
                <note type="curatorial">243-1</note>
                <address>
                <addrLine>Dr. Lucile Aly</addrLine>
                <addrLine>1138 22nd Ave., E.</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Eugene, Oregon</addrLine>
                </address>
                
                <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have just gotten out of the hospital after more than a week. I went there on Friday, the 13th (!) with a violent attack of pneumonia. They filled me up intravenously with a gallon of dextrose and forty-five million units of antibiotics. That ought to kill something, and it seems to have killed the pneumonia, leaving me pretty weak. I have also had innumberable "shots".</p>
                
                <p>I was very glad to hear that you would actually be here on May 30th and with the <hi rend="caps">MS</hi>. I am very eager to see you and to hear what you have written.</p>
                
                <p>This will be all for now, but let me hear from you. Give my best thoughts to Bower and Stewart.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>With the old affection for each of you,</salute>
                
                <signed>John N.</signed>
                
                <note>JGN:ENF</note>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
